=== 出版自由及印刷品審查制度 ===
在[[印刷術|印刷術]]發明之前，著作只能透過非常費力而且容易出錯的人手過程複製。由於沒有嚴格審查和控制[[書吏|書吏]]的系統，他們的作品很少引起廣泛爭議。1450年[[印刷機|印刷機]]出現之後，宗教權威所認為的[[異端|異端邪說]]得以傳播，[[羅馬天主教會|羅馬天主教會]]提出了審查制度。<ref name="de Sola Pool 1983 14">{{Cite book| last = de Sola Pool| first = Ithiel| title = Technologies of freedom| publisher = Harvard University Press| year = 1983| pages = 14| url = http://www.google.com/books?id=BzLXGUxV4CkC&pg=PA14&dq=%22Censorship+and+Control%22&redir_esc=y#v=onepage| isbn = 978-0-674-87233-2| access-date = 2013-02-07| archive-date = 2015-02-03| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150203012321/http://www.google.com/books?id=BzLXGUxV4CkC&pg=PA14&dq=%22Censorship+and+Control%22&redir_esc=y#v=onepage| dead-url = no}}</ref>新的[[印刷術|印刷術]]能準確地印制文字作品，使思想和資訊流通更加迅速和廣泛。<ref name="MacQueen 2007 34">{{Cite book | last = MacQueen | first = Hector L | coauthors = Charlotte Waelde and Graeme T Laurie | title = Contemporary Intellectual Property: Law and Policy | publisher = Oxford University Press | year = 2007 | pages = 34 | url = http://www.google.com/books?id=_Iwcn4pT0OoC&dq=contemporary+intellectual+property&source=gbs_navlinks_s | isbn = 978-0-19-926339-4 | access-date = 2013-02-07 | archive-date = 2012-01-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120105151614/http://www.google.com/books?id=_Iwcn4pT0OoC&dq=contemporary+intellectual+property&source=gbs_navlinks_s | dead-url = no }}</ref>1501年，[[亞歷山大六世|教宗亞歷山大六世]]頒布一條針對無牌印刷書籍的法案，並在1559年首次發出[[禁書目錄|禁書目錄]]。<ref name="de Sola Pool 1983 14"/>羅馬天主教會的禁書目錄主要是為了控制民眾思想和意見，打壓違背教會教義和意見的觀點，其中包括禁止或[[审查制度|審查]][[笛卡爾|笛卡爾]]、[[焦爾達諾·布魯諾|焦爾達諾·布魯諾]]、[[伽利略|伽利略]]、[[大衛·休謨|大衛·休謨]]、[[約翰·洛克|約翰·洛克]]、[[丹尼爾·笛福|丹尼爾·笛福]]、[[让-雅克·卢梭|让-雅克·卢梭]]及[[伏爾泰|伏爾泰]]等人的著作。<ref>{{Cite book| last = Castillo| first = Anastasia| title = Banned Books: Censorship in Eighteenth-Century England| publisher = GRIN Verlag| year = 2010| pages = 12| url = http://books.google.com/?id=CqaAGfL-IQIC&dq=Giordano+Bruno+censorship| isbn = 978-3-640-71688-3}}</ref>因為印刷業使[[聖經|聖經]]和政府的信息得以流通，教會和政府在很多方面都支持印刷業，但與此同時，不同意見和批評教會和政府的作品也可以迅速流通傳播。因此，為了控制整個歐洲的印刷者，當局要求他們得到官方授權才可生產和交易書本。<ref name="MacQueen 2007 34"/>

[[File:Index_Librorum_Prohibitorum_1.jpg|thumb]]出版的[[禁書目錄|禁書目錄]]的封面。]]

隨着[[新聞媒體|新聞媒體]]和[[印刷|印刷]]的發展，應該允許表達異見或顛覆性的意見，而不受到懲罰或法律制裁的概念也隨之興起。1644年，英國思想家[[約翰·彌爾頓|約翰·彌爾頓]]出版一本反對審查制度的短論《[[论出版自由|论出版自由]]》，以回應議會重新引入對印刷者的發牌制度。<ref name="Sanders 2003 66"/>[[教廷|教廷]]當局此前曾拒絕對彌爾頓的一篇關於離婚權利的著作發出出版許可證，而《[[论出版自由|论出版自由]]》則在沒有許可下發行。<ref>{{Cite web| title = 13. John Milton（1608–1674）Areopagitica; A Speech  of Mr. John Milton  for the Liberty of  Unlicenc’d Printing，to the  Parlament of England. London: [s.n.]，1644| work = Early Censorship in England，“Heresy and Error”: The Ecclesiastical Censorship of Books，1400-1800| publisher = Bridwell Library| date = Exhibition September 20 – December 17，2000| url = http://smu.edu/bridwell_tools/specialcollections/Heresy&Error/Heresy.13.htm| accessdate = 2011-06-26| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120905104556/http://smu.edu/bridwell_tools/specialcollections/Heresy%26Error/Heresy.13.htm| archivedate = 2012-09-05| deadurl = yes}}</ref>彌爾頓發表了慷慨激昂的表達自由和容忍的謬誤呼籲：<ref name="Sanders 2003 66">{{Cite book| last = Sanders| first = Karen| title = Ethics & Journalism| publisher = Sage| year = 2003| pages = 66| url = http://www.google.com/books?id=bnpliIUyO60C&dq=Areopagitica+freedom+of+speech+britain&lr=&as_brr=3&source=gbs_navlinks_s| isbn = 978-0-7619-6967-9| access-date = 2013-02-07| archive-date = 2015-01-25| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150125042844/http://www.google.com/books?id=bnpliIUyO60C&dq=Areopagitica+freedom+of+speech+britain&lr=&as_brr=3&source=gbs_navlinks_s| dead-url = no}}</ref> 
